The paper deals with document exchange protocols, which involve efficient algorithms for transmitting and reconstructing files. This falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the size of summaries and codes, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and data compression (cs.DC). The paper also mentions randomized and derandomized protocols, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses error-correcting codes, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
